  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Autumn Floods
---
The millepede said, "You don't understand. Haven't you ever watched a
man spit? He just gives a hawk and out it comes, some drops as big as
pearls, some as fine as mist, raining down in a jumble of countless
particles. Now all I do is put in motion the heavenly mechanism in me -
I'm not aware of how the thing works."
